stylometry: The concept of a logical upper limit is a solution in which reaches the upper portion of the possible solution.  It is the obvious solution at the maximum capability based on the information you have in the current model.  You need one of these to be able to base your other information and answers off of this logical upper limit.  If you dont find answers to other questions you can use it as a guide to help you solve a problem based on the constraints in the problem.  For example if I am selling exercise rubber bands that cost 25 dollars and the total cost of purchasing the rubber bands was 500 dollars  What is the logical upper limit if I have sold 500 of these rubber bands.  The logical upper limit would be the 25 dollars mulitplied by the 500 you have solde minus the total cost.  That would be the logical upper limit in profit.  WHen other constraints enter the problem is when the logical upper limit can be used as a guide.
